premise_source_doc_sentence: The Slovak Soviet Republic  (  Slovak : Slovenská republika rád , Hungarian : Szlovák Tanácsköztársaság , Ukrainian : Словацька Радянська Республіка , literally : `` Slovak Republic of Councils '' - the name originated before the Russian word `` Soviet ''  (  council  )  became widespread in Slovak and other languages include Hungarian and Ukrainian  )  comprised a very short-lived Communist state in southeast Slovakia from 16 June to 7 July 1919 with its capital city in Prešov .
